The Monkey and the Crocodile Summary will take us through the poetic version of the children’s tale which has the same name. It is about a crocodile who lives in a river. He becomes friends with a monkey that lives on a tree on the river bank. Consequently, the monkey shares the fruits of the tree with his friend, the crocodile. Further, the crocodile takes a share for his wife. 
However, he has a greedy wife is not after the sweetness of the fruit but that of the monkey’s heart. She convinces the crocodile to bring the monkey home, which he does. But he decides not to betray his friend and tells him the truth.